&lt;p&gt;Feeling and Thinking are two different process in human  &lt;br&gt;
And both work from different parts of the human brain.  &lt;br&gt;
Metaphorically people say  &lt;br&gt;
thinking is from the head and feeling from heart.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;People say when in conflict between head and heart  &lt;br&gt;
then listen to the heart and not head.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Think deeper, ask yourself  &lt;br&gt;
can you think without feeling anything? &lt;br&gt;
If that is possible then how it is possible that  &lt;br&gt;
you think about some past event and you become emotional?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
